                     <hi rend="largeCaps">CHARLES HARRISON</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18501125-157-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18501125-157-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18501125-157-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>, stealing 3 handkerchiefs, 1 sovereign, 1 half-sovereign, and 10 shillings; the property of <persName id="t18501125-name-891" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-891" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-891" type="surname" value="GIBSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-891" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18501125-157-offence-1 t18501125-name-891"></join>Thomas Gibson</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18501125-name-892" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-892" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-892" type="surname" value="GIBSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-892" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS GIBSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the 5th batallion of Royal Artillery, Woolwich. The prisoner was in my department. On 27th Oct., at a quarter to six o'clock, I left the barrack-room, leaving my clothes and money safe in my box—I returned at half-past eight, and found my box broken open, and three handkerchiefs, a sovereign, half-sovereign, half-crowns, shillings, sixpences, and four penny pieces gone—the prisoner slept in that room—he was absent when the roll was called, at half-past eight—next morning I went with Walker to a brothel in Wool<lb></lb>wich, and found the prisoner there, in bed, and my three handkerchiefs in his coat-pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Was the door locked when you went out? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18501125-name-893" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-893" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-893" type="surname" value="WALKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-893" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WALKER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, K</hi> 298). I went with Gibson, and found the prisoner in bed with a prostitute—these three handkerchiefs were in his jacket-pocket, and a half-sovereign, two half-crowns, two shillings, and a sixpence between the bed and the mattress.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I found the handkerchiefs at the door, and put them into my pocket; the money I had I won at cards.</p>
               <p>
